FastStream is an open-source framework for building asynchronous web services that interact with event streams. It provides a unified API to work with multiple message brokers like Kafka, RabbitMQ, NATS, and Redis. Key features include Pydantic validation, automatic AsyncAPI documentation, full-typed editor support, a powerful dependency injection system, support for in-memory tests, and compatibility with any HTTP framework, especially FastAPI. FastStream is optimized for automatic code generation using advanced models like GPT and Llama.

FastStream is an open-source framework for building asynchronous web services that interact with event streams. It provides a unified API to work with multiple message brokers like Kafka, RabbitMQ, NATS, and Redis. Key features include Pydantic validation, automatic AsyncAPI documentation, full-typed editor support, powerful dependency injection system, support for in-memory tests, and compatibility with any HTTP framework, especially FastAPI. FastStream is optimized for automatic code generation using advanced models like GPT and Llama.

Key features include Pydantic validation, automatic AsyncAPI documentation, full-typed editor support, a powerful dependency injection system, in-memory testing, extensibility, and compatibility with HTTP frameworks such as FastAPI. The framework is also designed for automatic code generation with models like GPT and Llama. Due to technical issues, additional details about tutorials, code API, contributing guidelines, and release notes are not accessible.
